The course is part of the semiotics and culture studies BA curriculum and is based in its framework and objectives on the general objective of the curriculum, "To train interdisciplinarily educated culture analysts who can use both theoretical and practical methods". Hence the course focuses on developing skills of analysing various kinds of texts, paying most attention to traditional, foremost literary translation texts, as well as intersemiotic translation.
The course combines the format of lectures and seminars.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce translation as a research object from the viewpoint of semiotics of translation and translation studies; to develop skills of analysing translations; to provide an overview of translation studies and semiotics of translation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course is able to analyse different types of translations created on the basis different types of texts, to evaluate the translatability of various texts; is able to detect possible translation problems and search for their solutions.
